Okay.

496
00:21:20,329 --> 00:21:21,940
Okay, I've gotta go in and
do an embolectomy on this leg.

497
00:21:21,964 --> 00:21:23,392
Uh-uh. No. I gotta
go in and fix his heart.

498
00:21:23,416 --> 00:21:25,059
You can do that later.
I need to do this now.

499
00:21:25,083 --> 00:21:27,195
Later? It's already later.
He has lost blood flow!

500
00:21:27,219 --> 00:21:29,347
He's clearly throwing
emboli into his extremities.

501
00:21:29,371 --> 00:21:30,832
And where do you think
the emboli is coming from?

502
00:21:30,856 --> 00:21:31,884
His infected heart. Cristina...

503
00:21:31,908 --> 00:21:33,507
Hey, hey, hey!

504
00:21:33,576 --> 00:21:35,137
I can hear you two from all
the way the damn hallway.

505
00:21:35,161 --> 00:21:36,855
Will you tell Callie to back
off and let me do my job?

506
00:21:36,879 --> 00:21:38,223
Yeah, tell Cristina to back
off and let me do mine.

507
00:21:38,247 --> 00:21:40,375
If I don't try this embolectomy,
he could lose his leg.

508
00:21:40,399 --> 00:21:42,794
He can live without a leg. He
can't live without a functioning heart.

509
00:21:42,818 --> 00:21:44,146
Look, if you do
the heart tomorrow,

510
00:21:44,170 --> 00:21:46,065
it gives him an extra day
on antibiotics, all right?

511
00:21:46,089 --> 00:21:48,583
He'll be more stable, and the
heart surgery will be less risky.

512
00:21:48,607 --> 00:21:51,169
Cristina, this is Travis
Reed we're talking about.

513
00:21:51,193 --> 00:21:52,637
Let me try to save his leg.

514
00:21:52,661 --> 00:21:55,196
Dr. Torres performed the
embolectomy that afternoon.

515
00:21:55,264 --> 00:21:56,897
Against your wishes?

516
00:21:56,966 --> 00:21:59,199
We had a professional
difference of opinion.

517
00:21:59,268 --> 00:22:00,478
You know, in my office,

518
00:22:00,502 --> 00:22:03,437
if one of my co-workers
was shouting at me so loudly

519
00:22:03,505 --> 00:22:05,050
that you could hear him
all the way down the hall,

520
00:22:05,074 --> 00:22:07,169
it would be more than
just a difference of opinion.

521
00:22:07,193 --> 00:22:08,503
It would be grounds
for a dismissal.

522
00:22:08,527 --> 00:22:11,445
We are passionate
about our work.

523
00:22:11,513 --> 00:22:14,181
And in the end, I
agreed with Dr. Torres,

524
00:22:14,250 --> 00:22:15,849
that the heart
surgery could wait.

525
00:22:15,918 --> 00:22:17,438
You agreed? Yes.

526
00:22:17,486 --> 00:22:19,148
Are you sure you
weren't bullied? Objection.

527
00:22:19,172 --> 00:22:20,571
Yeah, I know.

528
00:22:20,639 --> 00:22:21,950
The embolectomy could
not have gone better.

529
00:22:21,974 --> 00:22:23,152
I mean, his leg was
already pinking up

530
00:22:23,176 --> 00:22:24,553
by the time I saw him
in recovery last night.

531
00:22:24,577 --> 00:22:25,976
What's his temp?

532
00:22:26,045 --> 00:22:28,173
Oh, he was febrile overnight,
but his white count's stable.

533
00:22:28,197 --> 00:22:29,529
All right.

534
00:22:31,650 --> 00:22:33,217
What's going on? Travis?

535
00:22:33,285 --> 00:22:36,125
What aren't you telling
me? What's wrong?

536
00:22:38,424 --> 00:22:40,624
What the hell is
wrong with my legs?

537
00:22:49,735 --> 00:22:51,763
Are we losing this case?
It's too early to panic.

538
00:22:51,787 --> 00:22:53,564
We haven't presented our side.

539
00:22:53,588 --> 00:22:55,706
There she is.

540
00:22:55,775 --> 00:22:58,175
Richard! You shouldn't be here.

541
00:22:58,244 --> 00:23:01,078
That's what I told him,
but he insisted on coming.

542
00:23:01,146 --> 00:23:04,048
It's a miracle I made it here
at all. Kepner's a terrible driver.

543
00:23:05,484 --> 00:23:07,168
How's it going?

544
00:23:07,236 --> 00:23:09,736
<i>You knew it was bad.</i>

545
00:23:09,805 --> 00:23:12,640
His legs were black.
I knew it wasn't good.

546
00:23:13,659 --> 00:23:15,559
They cut them off that night.

547
00:23:15,627 --> 00:23:16,938
Now, did you have any indication

548
00:23:16,962 --> 00:23:18,390
that Dr. Torres was even worried

549
00:23:18,414 --> 00:23:20,175
about something like amputation?

550
00:23:20,199 --> 00:23:22,210
I mean, did she ever mention
that it might be even a risk?

551
00:23:22,234 --> 00:23:25,603
No. But she was
worried about it.

552
00:23:25,671 --> 00:23:28,055
She was worried about what
it would do to her reputation.

553
00:23:28,124 --> 00:23:29,634
What is she talking about?

554
00:23:29,658 --> 00:23:31,637
Now, why would you
say that? I have no idea.

555
00:23:31,661 --> 00:23:33,510
I heard her talking
in the hallway.

556
00:23:33,579 --> 00:23:35,462
She didn't know
I could hear her.

557
00:23:35,531 --> 00:23:36,747
What did she say?

558
00:23:39,202 --> 00:23:40,779
<i>She said, "I can't be the doctor</i>

559
00:23:40,803 --> 00:23:43,420
<i>"who turns an Olympic
athlete into a doorstop."</i>

560
00:23:45,057 --> 00:23:48,158
All right, quiet down!
Quiet down, everyone!

561
00:23:48,878 --> 00:23:50,277
Quiet down!

562
00:23:50,346 --> 00:23:52,046
<i>Do we knock?</i>

563
00:23:52,114 --> 00:23:54,059
No, there's an open house on
Sunday. We can come back then.

564
00:23:54,083 --> 00:23:55,944
Oh, oh! There's a swing set.

565
00:23:55,968 --> 00:23:57,980
Oh, and a pool! A pool!
Callie, there's a pool!

566
00:23:58,004 --> 00:23:59,948
Ooh! Yeah? Yeah.

567
00:23:59,972 --> 00:24:03,035
Oh, I can just see us playing
with the girls in this yard,

568
00:24:03,059 --> 00:24:06,093
having a picnic and
swinging on the swings.

569
00:24:06,162 --> 00:24:08,311
Oh. What makes you think
we're having another girl?

570
00:24:08,380 --> 00:24:09,897
Come on.

571
00:24:09,966 --> 00:24:11,676
Can you get off of that
thing for five seconds

572
00:24:11,700 --> 00:24:13,033
and look at this place?

573
00:24:13,119 --> 00:24:14,429
Yeah, I know, hold on
a second. I'm just, uh...

574
00:24:14,453 --> 00:24:15,630
I'm following up
on that clinical trial

575
00:24:15,654 --> 00:24:16,998
in Germany using
Peterson hip joints.

576
00:24:17,022 --> 00:24:18,634
I'm trying to get them
to send me their data.

577
00:24:18,658 --> 00:24:20,602
Well, they're not gonna release
anything until it's published.

578
00:24:20,626 --> 00:24:22,259
Eh. It's worth a shot.

579
00:24:23,178 --> 00:24:24,658
There, sent.

580
00:24:24,713 --> 00:24:25,412
All right, now you can
show me the swing set.

581
00:24:25,481 --> 00:24:26,696
Okay. Oh! Ooh.

582
00:24:26,765 --> 00:24:27,875
You okay? Yeah.

583
00:24:27,899 --> 00:24:29,394
You all right? I got it.

584
00:24:29,418 --> 00:24:30,467
<i>I've got it.</i>

585
00:24:51,307 --> 00:24:52,917
Do you swear to tell
the truth, the whole truth,

586
00:24:52,941 --> 00:24:54,981
and nothing but the truth? I do.

587
00:24:57,313 --> 00:24:59,193
Hey, Travis. Hey.

588
00:25:00,166 --> 00:25:02,166
You know, I'm, uh...

589
00:25:02,234 --> 00:25:04,668
I'm thinking about snowboarding.

590
00:25:04,737 --> 00:25:07,037
In fact, I picked up a
board, a Burton Blunt.

591
00:25:07,105 --> 00:25:09,301
You familiar with that
one? That's a good board.

592
00:25:09,325 --> 00:25:10,502
There's better
boards for beginners.

593
00:25:10,526 --> 00:25:12,009
What size shoe are you?

594
00:25:12,077 --> 00:25:13,494
I'm a 13.

595
00:25:13,579 --> 00:25:15,407
You might wanna
look into an extra wide,

596
00:25:15,431 --> 00:25:17,225
so your toes don't
hang over too much.

597
00:25:17,249 --> 00:25:19,661
A little overhang's fine, but
too much is gonna cause drag.

598
00:25:19,685 --> 00:25:21,079
And drag's bad? Well...

599
00:25:21,103 --> 00:25:22,598
Objection, Your Honor.
Where's this going?

600
00:25:22,622 --> 00:25:24,883
Look, I'm simply consulting
an expert on snowboarding

601
00:25:24,907 --> 00:25:25,972
about a snowboard.

602
00:25:26,041 --> 00:25:27,608
I mean, who should I trust more,

603
00:25:27,676 --> 00:25:29,676
this guy or the kid who's
helping me out at REI?

604
00:25:29,745 --> 00:25:31,990
Get to the point, Mr. Hamilton.

605
00:25:32,014 --> 00:25:35,032
Travis, when you
first met Dr. Torres,

606
00:25:35,101 --> 00:25:36,595
did you ask her about
a certain kind of joint?

607
00:25:36,619 --> 00:25:39,915
The Peterson joint. I'd
heard it was good for athletes.

608
00:25:39,939 --> 00:25:41,750
Quicker recovery,
better range of motion.

609
00:25:41,774 --> 00:25:45,075
So you were consulting an
expert on joint replacement

610
00:25:45,144 --> 00:25:46,638
about a joint? Yeah.

611
00:25:46,662 --> 00:25:49,046
Is it true that Dr. Torres
had never actually done

612
00:25:49,114 --> 00:25:50,914
an operation with this
kind of joint before?

613
00:25:50,950 --> 00:25:52,744
It's true. But you went
ahead with it anyway.

614
00:25:52,768 --> 00:25:54,245
She said she had
done a lot of research.

615
00:25:54,269 --> 00:25:55,714
She said she was confident.

616
00:25:55,738 --> 00:25:59,372
So you trusted her to use
her expertise to advise you

617
00:25:59,441 --> 00:26:01,007
and to keep you safe.

618
00:26:01,076 --> 00:26:04,344
When, in fact, what you
got was a botched surgery,

619
00:26:04,430 --> 00:26:08,098
an infection, a revision
surgery, a heart surgery, and...

620
00:26:11,370 --> 00:26:13,070
I mean, look at you now.

621
00:26:13,138 --> 00:26:15,658
<i>Just let me pull up the blanket.</i>

622
00:26:16,675 --> 00:26:19,877
Why? So you don't
have to look at them?

623
00:26:19,945 --> 00:26:22,479
There's nothing there.

624
00:26:28,103 --> 00:26:29,436
Is it her?

625
00:26:34,577 --> 00:26:35,642
Hey, Travis.

626
00:26:35,711 --> 00:26:36,926
Tell her to go.

627
00:26:36,995 --> 00:26:39,396
I don't wanna see her. I
don't wanna talk to her.

628
00:26:42,968 --> 00:26:44,367
Um...

629
00:26:44,437 --> 00:26:47,187
I just brought you some
information on support groups.

630
00:26:47,255 --> 00:26:48,855
Um, try to get him to go.

631
00:26:48,924 --> 00:26:50,324
And, on the back,

632
00:26:50,392 --> 00:26:52,220
there's a name of an
incredible prosthetist...

633
00:26:52,244 --> 00:26:53,911
Tell her to get out.

634
00:26:53,979 --> 00:26:55,219
<i>I trusted her.</i>

635
00:26:56,431 --> 00:26:59,583
I trusted her completely, and...

636
00:26:59,652 --> 00:27:02,230
You know, I get that
people live without legs

637
00:27:02,254 --> 00:27:04,374
and it's not the
end of the world,

638
00:27:06,025 --> 00:27:08,592
but it's the end of my world.

639
00:27:08,660 --> 00:27:10,238
I've been snowboarding
since I was five.

640
00:27:10,262 --> 00:27:12,374
I used to steal cafeteria
trays from school

641
00:27:12,398 --> 00:27:14,309
and ride 'em down
my parents' driveway.

642
00:27:14,333 --> 00:27:16,633
Snow or no snow, I didn't care.

643
00:27:16,702 --> 00:27:18,680
It was the thing I did for fun.

644
00:27:18,704 --> 00:27:21,505
Then it became my
job and my world.

645
00:27:21,574 --> 00:27:26,260
And now it's everything.
My family, my friends.

646
00:27:26,328 --> 00:27:29,896
Without it, I don't
know who I am.

647
00:27:31,867 --> 00:27:34,107
And now it's gone. It's just...

648
00:27:36,588 --> 00:27:37,688
Gone.

649
00:27:44,396 --> 00:27:46,396
And it's Dr. Torres' fault.

650
00:27:53,906 --> 00:27:55,306
You feel very
strongly about that.

651
00:27:55,374 --> 00:27:56,873
It's not just a feeling.

652
00:27:56,942 --> 00:27:58,509
I know it. She told me.

653
00:27:58,577 --> 00:28:00,511
What, she admitted
that she was at fault?

654
00:28:00,579 --> 00:28:02,512
Yes, she did.

655
00:28:02,581 --> 00:28:04,882
The day she cut off my
legs, she came into my room,

656
00:28:04,950 --> 00:28:06,432
she'd been crying.

657
00:28:06,501 --> 00:28:08,679
She told me she
was sorry. Objection!

658
00:28:08,703 --> 00:28:10,721
It is illegal to use a
physician's apology

659
00:28:10,789 --> 00:28:12,334
against them as
evidence of guilt.

660
00:28:12,358 --> 00:28:14,975
Your Honor, this isn't
about the apology.

661
00:28:15,043 --> 00:28:18,895
This is about everything
else she said with the apology.

662
00:28:18,964 --> 00:28:20,531
I'll allow it.

663
00:28:23,702 --> 00:28:26,903
Travis, I know this is gonna be
painful, so you take your time.

664
00:28:29,008 --> 00:28:32,659
What else did Dr. Torres say?

665
00:28:32,728 --> 00:28:35,968
She said if there was
anyone to blame, it was her.

666
00:28:37,482 --> 00:28:39,344
She said this never
should've happened.

667
00:28:39,368 --> 00:28:42,597
She said if there was any way
she could change things, she would.

668
00:28:42,621 --> 00:28:44,721
Those were her exact words?

669
00:28:47,309 --> 00:28:48,842
Yes, they were.

670
00:28:55,217 --> 00:28:57,384
The prosecution rests.

671
00:29:08,313 --> 00:29:09,991
Yes, we had so much fun today.

672
00:29:10,015 --> 00:29:11,281
Big hugs.

673
00:29:11,349 --> 00:29:12,682
I love you. I love you.

674
00:29:12,752 --> 00:29:13,984
I know.

675
00:29:14,053 --> 00:29:16,419
Okay, all right, honey.
I'll see you soon.

676
00:29:16,488 --> 00:29:17,915
Hey, your dad's making
me a little nervous.

677
00:29:17,939 --> 00:29:19,083
Yeah, you should
probably go now.

678
00:29:19,107 --> 00:29:20,590
Definitely go now.

679
00:29:20,659 --> 00:29:21,958
Bye! Bye!

680
00:29:22,011 --> 00:29:23,643
Bye-bye. Bye-bye!

681
00:29:26,114 --> 00:29:28,781
Thank you for not
saying anything to her.

682
00:29:30,585 --> 00:29:32,763
If my grandbaby hadn't
been standing right there,

683
00:29:32,787 --> 00:29:34,666
believe me, I
would've said plenty.

684
00:29:34,690 --> 00:29:37,591
Dad, don't start right now.
I have to be in court soon.

685
00:29:37,660 --> 00:29:39,221
I have to take the stand
today, and I'm just...

686
00:29:39,245 --> 00:29:41,189
Your mother and I have
been married 38 years.

687
00:29:41,213 --> 00:29:42,824
You think it's been
easy? No, don't.

688
00:29:42,848 --> 00:29:44,109
You think we
haven't had troubles?

689
00:29:44,133 --> 00:29:45,965
Don't do that. Don't
start comparing. Don't.

690
00:29:46,034 --> 00:29:48,813
What happened to her "good
man in a storm" baloney?

691
00:29:48,837 --> 00:29:50,336
It's not right.

692
00:29:50,406 --> 00:29:51,850
She should be here
every day trying to fix it.

693
00:29:51,874 --> 00:29:53,239
It's not like that.

694
00:29:53,308 --> 00:29:55,219
Oh, no? The hell it isn't.

695
00:29:55,243 --> 00:29:58,061
She hurt you, and now she's too
much of a coward to even face you.

696
00:29:58,130 --> 00:29:59,641
Now she's running away,
abandoning her family.

697
00:29:59,665 --> 00:30:02,549
No, she's not running away,
all right? I kicked her out.

698
00:30:02,618 --> 00:30:04,484
It was my choice to
split up. It was mine.

699
00:30:04,553 --> 00:30:06,986
All right, so just
drop it, okay?

700
00:30:07,055 --> 00:30:08,899
You chose to break
up your family?

701
00:30:08,923 --> 00:30:10,640
Dad, not now.

702
00:30:13,545 --> 00:30:14,990
Did you even try
to work things out?

703
00:30:15,014 --> 00:30:16,846
Dad.

704
00:30:16,915 --> 00:30:18,360
<i>I knew what I was doing.</i>

705
00:30:18,384 --> 00:30:20,628
I did extensive research
on the Peterson hip.

706
00:30:20,652 --> 00:30:22,953
I even spoke with the
team who invented it.

707
00:30:23,021 --> 00:30:26,034
Everyone agreed that
Travis was an ideal candidate.

708
00:30:26,058 --> 00:30:29,293
And the surgery?
It went smoothly?

709
00:30:29,361 --> 00:30:32,912
The cut position and the
femoral resurfacing were perfect.

710
00:30:32,981 --> 00:30:34,114
What wasn't perfect?

711
00:30:34,182 --> 00:30:36,900
At the end of surgery,
the patient desatted,

712
00:30:36,969 --> 00:30:39,085
which means his
oxygen level went down

713
00:30:39,154 --> 00:30:40,632
and his heart was
beating really fast,

714
00:30:40,656 --> 00:30:42,922
which is really dangerous.

715
00:30:42,991 --> 00:30:44,819
We thought he might
have a clot in his lungs,

716
00:30:44,843 --> 00:30:46,988
so it was vital that we
finish the surgery quickly.

717
00:30:47,012 --> 00:30:49,707
And that's when you
left the sponge. Yes.

718
00:30:49,731 --> 00:30:51,197
And I would do it again.

719
00:30:54,753 --> 00:30:57,153
The patient's life was at risk.

720
00:30:57,222 --> 00:30:59,684
I believe that the sponge
wouldn't compromise the joint.

721
00:30:59,708 --> 00:31:02,392
I made a call, and I was right.

722
00:31:02,460 --> 00:31:03,810
It was the right call.

723
00:31:03,879 --> 00:31:07,197
So leaving the sponge was
deliberate. Not a mistake.

724
00:31:07,266 --> 00:31:10,067
You weren't being
careless or distracted.

725
00:31:10,135 --> 00:31:12,163
<i>Make sure his BP and
O-2 sats stay stable.</i>

726
00:31:12,187 --> 00:31:14,899
And bring me his post-op
X-ray. I wanna locate that sponge.

727
00:31:14,923 --> 00:31:15,956
Got it.

728
00:31:17,910 --> 00:31:19,058
Oh!

729
00:31:19,127 --> 00:31:21,194
You missed our appointment. Hmm?

730
00:31:22,330 --> 00:31:23,997
Oh, damn it!

731
00:31:24,083 --> 00:31:25,965
I'm so sorry.

732
00:31:26,034 --> 00:31:28,262
My surgery went long, and I
completely forgot. How'd it go?

733
00:31:28,286 --> 00:31:30,031
I mean, I know the ultrasound's
just a blob at this point,

734
00:31:30,055 --> 00:31:31,488
but still.

735
00:31:31,557 --> 00:31:33,557
Did you get a
picture of the blob?

736
00:31:34,509 --> 00:31:36,242
There's no picture.

737
00:31:37,111 --> 00:31:38,762
And no heartbeat.

738
00:31:39,464 --> 00:31:40,730
What?

739
00:31:40,799 --> 00:31:44,984
She did the ultrasound and
she looked and she looked.

740
00:31:45,053 --> 00:31:47,036
But there's no heartbeat.

741
00:31:50,508 --> 00:31:53,710
We lost the baby?

742
00:31:53,779 --> 00:31:57,747
<i>I remember the day very
clearly. I wasn't distracted.</i>

743
00:31:57,816 --> 00:32:00,283
