803
00:34:51,406 --> 00:34:54,890
But Whitney has
nothing to do with that.

804
00:34:54,959 --> 00:34:56,571
You wanna take your
crap out on somebody,

805
00:34:56,595 --> 00:34:58,489
you take it out on me,
all right? I can handle it.

806
00:34:58,513 --> 00:35:00,975
You need somebody to
blame? Then blame me.

807
00:35:00,999 --> 00:35:02,999
Go on. Yell all you want.

808
00:35:07,172 --> 00:35:09,872
This never should've
happened to you.

809
00:35:09,941 --> 00:35:13,660
And if there were any way that
I could magically change things,

810
00:35:13,728 --> 00:35:15,495
believe me, I would.

811
00:35:16,965 --> 00:35:19,246
I wish there was
something I could do.

812
00:35:19,785 --> 00:35:21,751
I wish I could fix this.

813
00:35:26,258 --> 00:35:30,393
I tried. I tried so hard.

814
00:35:32,364 --> 00:35:34,404
I'm so sorry, Travis.

815
00:35:35,467 --> 00:35:38,451
I'm so, so sorry.

816
00:35:40,588 --> 00:35:42,255
<i>Yes, I apologized.</i>

817
00:35:43,291 --> 00:35:46,359
I understood what
Travis was feeling.

818
00:35:46,427 --> 00:35:47,839
I went through the
same thing with my wife.

819
00:35:47,863 --> 00:35:53,650
She lost her leg last year,
and, um, it's changed us.

820
00:35:53,718 --> 00:35:58,188
It's, uh, cost us in ways that I
can't even begin to understand.

821
00:35:59,407 --> 00:36:03,343
I wouldn't wish this
experience on anyone.

822
00:36:03,412 --> 00:36:05,528
And now it was
happening to my patient.

823
00:36:05,597 --> 00:36:07,464
Of course I was sorry.

824
00:36:08,867 --> 00:36:10,433
I still am.

825
00:36:10,502 --> 00:36:13,486
I'm so, so sorry this
happened to you, Travis.

826
00:36:13,555 --> 00:36:17,974
That makes me human. That
does not make me negligent.

827
00:36:18,043 --> 00:36:21,055
And if I can't feel for my
patients without getting sued,

828
00:36:21,079 --> 00:36:22,857
then I guess I'm just
gonna keep on getting sued,

829
00:36:22,881 --> 00:36:24,714
because that's who I am.

830
00:36:25,650 --> 00:36:27,750
I won't apologize for that.

831
00:36:33,292 --> 00:36:35,825
Dad, we're home. We're back.

832
00:36:35,894 --> 00:36:39,762
Oh, I guess he's still out
in the park with the girls.

833
00:36:39,831 --> 00:36:42,543
How long do you think it's gonna
take for the jury to come back?

834
00:36:42,567 --> 00:36:46,536
I don't know. Could be
days, sometimes weeks.

835
00:36:46,605 --> 00:36:48,037
What's that?

836
00:36:48,106 --> 00:36:52,959
I think it's from a clinical
trial on the Peterson hip.

837
00:36:53,028 --> 00:36:55,011
I thought I never heard back.

838
00:36:55,647 --> 00:36:57,346
Uh...

839
00:36:57,415 --> 00:36:59,015
"Enclosed is the
data you requested.

840
00:36:59,084 --> 00:37:01,596
"But please be advised, we've
currently put a stop to our trial.

841
00:37:01,620 --> 00:37:03,453
"There've been five
instances of infection

842
00:37:03,521 --> 00:37:06,322
"caused by the
pseudomonas bacteria.

843
00:37:06,391 --> 00:37:09,759
"We've traced the source
back to the Peterson joint."

844
00:37:10,696 --> 00:37:12,736
What's the postmark on that?

845
00:37:14,999 --> 00:37:16,966
Three weeks before
Travis' surgery.

846
00:37:21,506 --> 00:37:23,017
I can't just sit on this. I
have to tell them, right?

847
00:37:23,041 --> 00:37:25,908
I wouldn't. You didn't
willfully ignore any data.

848
00:37:25,977 --> 00:37:28,311
You didn't act
irresponsibly or maliciously.

849
00:37:28,380 --> 00:37:31,175
You worked off the
information you had at the time.

850
00:37:31,199 --> 00:37:33,277
And then an act of God happened.

851
00:37:33,301 --> 00:37:35,429
The letter fell
behind the bookcase.

852
00:37:35,453 --> 00:37:37,481
It could've just as easily
gotten lost in the mail.

853
00:37:37,505 --> 00:37:40,050
But it didn't. Accidents
happen. It's the job.

854
00:37:40,074 --> 00:37:42,253
This one happened in your
living room, not in the OR.

855
00:37:42,277 --> 00:37:44,977
You know, I was distracted.
I wasn't paying attention.

856
00:37:45,047 --> 00:37:46,557
I should've followed up
when I never heard back.

857
00:37:46,581 --> 00:37:48,409
You feel bad because
of what happened,

858
00:37:48,433 --> 00:37:49,732
and anybody would.

859
00:37:49,801 --> 00:37:51,495
But that envelope
is not a magic cure.

860
00:37:51,519 --> 00:37:53,397
It's not going to
grow his legs back.

861
00:37:53,421 --> 00:37:55,633
But what it could do,
it could sway a jury.

862
00:37:55,657 --> 00:37:57,968
It could make a jury
think differently about you,

